1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
FOR
4 HOUSE BILL NO. 3078 By: West (Josh)
5
6
7 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to veterans; imposing requirements on
executive governmental entities to provide
9 information related to certain donations; providing
for apportionment or deposit of amounts donated;
10 requiring government websites to provide information
related to certain donations; providing for
11 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
12
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7201 of Title 74, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. Each state agency, board, commission, department, or other
20 entity organized within the executive department shall include on
21 any of its forms as described by subsection B of this section a link
22 to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs or similar method in
23 order to allow a person making payment to such governmental entity
24
Req. No. 16342 Page 1

1 to m ake a donation to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs
2 Revolving Fund.
3 B. The provisions of this section shall include, but shall not
4 be limited to:
5 1. Driver license applications;
6 2. Motor vehicle registrations and renewals;
7 3. Fishing and hunting license applications;
8 4. Income tax forms; and
9 5. Any other transaction during which an executive agency
10 issues a license or utilizes a form that could contain the
11 information prescribed by subsection A of this section.
12 C. If payment for any item or service described in this section
13 can be made through a website owned or maintained on behalf of the
14 governmental entity, the website shall have a conspicuous area which
15 clearly indicates that the payor may utilize the website to make a
16 donation to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs Revolving
17 Fund.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
